//Process
// 1.) User clicks button, with an up and down animation
// 2.) If button is a number, it shows on the screen
// 3.) If the user has already clicked a number, the current is appended to the previous
// 4.) If the user clicks the +/- sign, the current value on screen is negated or made positive
// 5.) If the user clicks a math operator, it highlights the key
// 6.) When the user clicks another number, now the screen clears, and shows the new number to compute
// 6a.) Repeat 1-6
// 7.) If the user clicks =, the result is computed and displayed
// 7a.) User can continue to repeat 1 - 7
// 8.) If user clicks AC, the UI is reset

//Tasks
// 1.) Listen for click, trigger an animation function and input function
// 2.) Create an if/else statement to handle if the input is a number, clear, +/-, math operator, or equals sign
// 3.) Append each click number value together and update the UI each time according to the process above
// 4.) Create the functions for inputs clear, +/-, math oper
// 5.) Create the equals operator function

